## Optimization Summary - Q22 Iteration 3

### Bottleneck Identified
From execution_results.json (Iteration 2):
- **build_antijoin: 149.90 ms (59.6% of total time)** ← Critical bottleneck
- Total execution: 251.45 ms
- All other operations are well-optimized (<66 ms each)

### Root Cause Analysis
The previous iteration loaded a pre-built hash index (orders_o_custkey_hash.bin) in 66.35 ms but then **unnecessarily rebuilt the same data** into an `unordered_set` using parallel thread-local construction and merging, consuming an additional 149.90 ms.

### Optimizations Applied

**1. Removed Parallel Thread-Local Set Construction (HIGH IMPACT)**
   - **Before**: Parallel loop extracting hash index keys → thread-local accumulation → serial merge (expensive with 64 cores)
   - **After**: Single serial loop through hash index slots (256K slots, ~1.2 µs per slot)
   - **Expected savings**: ~80-100 ms (reduced from 149.90 ms to ~50-70 ms)
   - **Why it works**: The hash index already has all unique keys in slots; collecting them serially is faster than parallel coordination overhead

**2. Early Filtering in Scan Phase**
   - **Before**: String code construction happened before acctbal and antijoin checks
   - **After**: Code checks `acctbal > avg` and `NOT EXISTS orders` before string construction
   - **Expected savings**: ~3-5 ms (fewer string allocations on filtered-out rows)
   - **Why it works**: Most rows fail early filters; avoid allocating strings for rejected rows

### Expected Performance Impact
- **Previous total**: 251.45 ms
- **Expected new total**: ~170-190 ms (27-33% improvement)
- **Key improvements**:
  - build_antijoin: 149.90 ms → ~50-70 ms (66-68% reduction)
  - scan_filter_group: ~13.7 ms → ~10-12 ms (early filtering)

